sentence: Each legislator , after all , is only one out of 535 when it comes to national policy making .
mut.sentence: Each legislator, after all, is only one out of 535 when he or she comes to national policy making.
reason: 原句中的 'comes' 是一个固定短语 'when it comes to' 的组成部分，意思是 '当提到，当涉及到'，而变异句中的 'comes' 是动词的一般现在时形式，表示具体的动作 '来到，到达'，两者的含义和用法不同。

sentence: The crisis-hit US major banks are breaking free from their state shackles .
mut.sentence: The crisis-hit major banks in the US are breaking free from the shackles imposed by their state.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'state'的含义相同。在原句和变异句中，'state'都指的是与银行相关的政府或国家的权力机构，表示这些银行正在摆脱政府的限制或束缚。两个句子中的'state'没有体现出不同的含义。

sentence: The whole notion of `` creativity `` in education was ( and is ) part and parcel of a romantic rebellion against disciplined instruction , which was ( and is ) regarded as `` authoritarian , `` a repression and frustration of the latent talents and the wonderful , if as yet undefined , potentialities inherent in the souls of all our children .
mut.sentence: The entire concept of creativity in education was (and is) part and parcel of a romantic rebellion against disciplined instruction, which was (and is) seen as authoritarian, a repression and frustration of the latent talents and the wonderful, if as yet undefined, potentialities inherent in the souls of every single child.
reason: 原句和变异句中的目标词 'authoritarian' 在两个句子中的含义相同，都指代一种压制性的、强调纪律的教育方式，这种教育方式被认为是对孩子们潜在才能和潜力的抑制和挫败。两个句子中使用 'authoritarian' 的上下文没有变化，因此目标词的具体含义没有区别。

sentence: But the researchers found that the bacteria , discovered in Mono Lake , Calif. , is able to continue to grow after substituting arsenic for phosphorus .
mut.sentence: But the researchers found that the bacteria, discovered in Mono Lake, Calif., is able to continue to grow after substituting that element for phosphorus.
reason: 原句中明确指出细菌用砷（arsenic）取代了磷（phosphorus），而变异句中使用'that element'这一模糊指代，没有具体指明是砷，这改变了信息的具体性和明确性，因此两个句子中'bacteria'的含义有所不同。

sentence: Dr. Vogelstein next turned his attention colon cancer , the second biggest cancer killer in the U.S. after lung cancer .
mut.sentence: Dr. Vogelstein next turned his attention to colon cancer, which is the second biggest cancer killer in the U.S. after lung cancer.
reason: 原句和变异句中的'turned'都表示'转向，将注意力集中在'的意思，两个句子的目标词含义相同，没有发生变化。

sentence: When their changes are completed , and after they have worked up a sweat , ringers often skip off to the local pub , leaving worship for others below .
mut.sentence: When the changes are completed, and after the ringers have worked up sweat, the ringers often skip off to the local pub, leaving the worship for others below.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词 'leaving' 的含义是相同的。'Leaving' 在这里都表示一种动作，即指铃手们在完成工作后离开，把崇拜仪式留给其他人。原句中的 'leaving' 是现在分词形式，作为状语描述ringers的行为，而变异句中 'leaving' 也是同样的用法，没有改变其基本含义。因此，两个句子的目标词含义没有不同。

sentence: Each legislator , after all , is only one out of 535 when it comes to national policy making .
mut.sentence: Each legislator, after all, is only one out of 535 when he or she comes to national policy making.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'making'的含义并没有改变。'making'在两个句子中都是名词，作为'national policy'的定语，表示'制定'或'制作'的过程。原句和变异句中的差异在于从句引导词和主语的变化（'when it comes to' 与 'when he or she comes to'），但这并不影响'making'本身的含义。

sentence: Conversely , there are the majority of unsuccessful schools , and we know which efforts at educational reform are doomed beforehand .
mut.sentence: Conversely, there are the majority of unsuccessful schools, and we know which efforts at educational reform are destined to fail before they are initiated.
reason: 原句和变异句中的目标词'reform'的含义相同，都是指在教育领域中所做的改进和变革的努力。'doomed'和'destined to fail'在这里表达的是相同的概念，即这些改革尝试在开始之前就已经预见到可能会失败。

sentence: With membership of the Church of England steadily dwindling , strong-willed vicars are pressing equally strong-willed and often non-religious ringers to attend services .
mut.sentence: With the membership of the Church of England steadily dwindling, strong-willed vicars are pressing equally strong-willed and often non-religious individuals to attend services.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词 'vicars' 的含义没有改变，都是指英国圣公会中的牧师或教区神父。两个句子中 vicars 所指的角色和职责没有区别，变异句只是将 'ringers' 替换为 'individuals'，但这并不影响 'vicars' 的含义。

sentence: Mr. Baldwin is also attacking the greater problem : lack of ringers .
mut.sentence: Mr. Baldwin is also attacking this greater problem: lack of ringers.
reason: 原句和变异句中的目标词 'attacking' 在两个句子中的含义相同，都是指Mr. Baldwin正在积极对付或着手解决更大的问题，即缺乏铃声。两个句子中唯一的变化是变异句中加入了'this'这个词，但'this'在这里只是指代前文提到的同一个问题，并不改变'attacking'的含义。

sentence: When their changes are completed , and after they have worked up a sweat , ringers often skip off to the local pub , leaving worship for others below .
mut.sentence: When the changes are completed, and after the ringers have worked up sweat, the ringers often skip off to the local pub, leaving the worship for others below.
reason: 两个句子中的目标词'sweat'含义相同，都指的是通过劳动或运动而出汗。在两个句子中，'worked up a sweat'和'worked up sweat'是同义表达，都用来描述ringers（可能指的是教堂钟的敲钟人）在完成一些体力活动后出汗的情况。因此，目标词在这两个句子中的含义没有改变。

sentence: It gives a lot of flexibility to the process , said John Coequyt , senior Washington representative for the Sierra Club .
mut.sentence: This gives a lot of flexibility to the process, said John Coequyt, senior representative of Washington for the Sierra Club.
reason: 在原句中，'Washington'作为形容词使用，修饰'representative'，表示John Coequyt是Sierra Club在华盛顿的高级代表。而在变异句中，'Washington'作为名词使用，意味着John Coequyt是华盛顿这个地区的高级代表，这暗示了他代表的可能是华盛顿这个地方的利益，而非仅仅是Sierra Club在华盛顿的分支。因此，两个句子中的'Washington'在词性和意义上有所不同。

sentence: After this , only five exceeded the 30 games : Keilor Navas with 31 , Randall Azofeifa with 32 , Michael Barrantes with 31 , Carlos Hernandez with 36 and Jose Luis Lopez with 35 .
mut.sentence: After this period, only five players exceeded the 30 games mark: Keilor Navas with 31, Randall Azofeifa with 32, Michael Barrantes with 31, Carlos Hernandez with 36 and Jose Luis Lopez with 35.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词 'games' 的含义没有发生变化。在原句和变异句中，'games' 都指的是球员参加的比赛场次。变异句只是对原句进行了轻微的语法调整，将 'the 30 games' 改为 'the 30 games mark'，但这并不改变 'games' 的含义。

sentence: I 'd have to sell out my business to pay her off with her share .
mut.sentence: I'd have to sell out this business to pay her off with the share she is entitled to.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词 'pay' 的含义是相同的。'pay her off' 在两个句子中都是指支付某人应得的钱，无论是具体指代 'her share' 还是指代 'the share she is entitled to'，都表达了支付她应得份额的意思。因此，目标词 'pay' 的含义没有改变。

sentence: A more robust economic performance is reflected in rising support for private enterprise and the market economy : some 71 % of respondents across the region say that private enterprise is indispensable for development , up from 56 % in 2007 ( see chart 6 ) .
mut.sentence: A more robust economic performance is reflected in rising support for private enterprise and the market economy: some 71% of respondents across the region say that private enterprises are indispensable for development, up from 56% in 2007 (see chart number 6).
reason: 原句和变异句中的目标词'support'在语境中的含义相同，都指的是对私营企业和市场经济的支持态度或观点。两个句子中'support'的使用并没有因为句子结构的微小差异（如冒号后的标点符号或数字的表述方式）而改变其基本意义。

sentence: And it 's nothing that runs afoul of ethics rules .
mut.sentence: And this is nothing that runs afoul of ethics rules.
reason: 两个句子中的目标词'ethics'含义相同，都指的是行为规范、道德准则或专业伦理规则。原句和变异句只是通过改变引导词（And it's...变为And this is...），但并未改变目标词的含义。

sentence: Vicar Marshall admits to mixed feelings about this issue , since he is both a vicar and an active bell-ringer himself .
mut.sentence: Vicar Marshall admits to mixed feelings about the issue, since he is both a vicar and an active bell-ringer himself.
reason: 原句和变异句中的目标词 'feelings' 在两个句子中的含义没有变化，都指的是Vicar Marshall对于某个问题的复杂情感或感受。

sentence: Haney had n't given it much thought at the time .
mut.sentence: Haney hadn't given the situation much thought at the time.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'given'的含义相同，都表示'考虑到'或'思考到'。在原句中，'it'指代的是某个事物或想法，而在变异句中，'the situation'具体化了'it'的指代内容，但'given'作为动词在这里的含义并没有改变。

sentence: I want to study your landlord 's habits and movements first .
mut.sentence: I want to study the habits and movements of your landlord first.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词‘habits’的含义没有改变。‘habits’在原句和变异句中都指的是某人的习惯或行为模式，句子结构的变化（从‘your landlord's habits’到‘the habits of your landlord’）并没有影响到‘habits’这个词本身的含义。

sentence: Back in the chase car , we drove around some more , got stuck in a ditch , enlisted the aid of a local farmer to get out the trailer hitch and pull us out of the ditch .
mut.sentence: Back in the chase car, we drove around some more, got stuck in a ditch, enlisted the aid of a local farmer to get out the trailer hitch and pull the chase car out of the ditch.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词‘pull’的含义是相同的。‘pull’在这里指的是用力将车辆从沟渠中拉出。原句中提到‘pull us out of the ditch’，变异句中提到‘pull the chase car out of the ditch’，两者都描述了同样的动作，即拉出车辆，只是变异句中明确指出了是拉出追击车，但这个细节并不改变‘pull’这个词本身的含义。
